1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:04,671
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:09,843 --> 00:00:13,638
[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:15,974 --> 00:00:17,684
[Ibyang] <i>Did you find her?</i>

4
00:00:17,767 --> 00:00:19,394
<i>Why aren’t you with her?</i>

5
00:00:19,477 --> 00:00:22,480
[Atoy] <i>I’ll handle it. Don’t meddle, okay?</i>

6
00:00:22,564 --> 00:00:25,358
<i>I need a disguise to get</i>
<i>inside Endless Nights.</i>

7
00:00:25,442 --> 00:00:27,277
[Cita] <i>Tonet might be able to help you.</i>

8
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:29,070
[Lorna] <i>Okay, bring that inside.</i>

9
00:00:29,154 --> 00:00:31,281
<i>Where are our additional janitors?</i>

10
00:00:31,364 --> 00:00:32,657
[guard] <i>They’re not here yet, Ma’am Lorna.</i>

11
00:00:32,741 --> 00:00:34,743
<i>But the agency already called.</i>
<i>They said they’re on the way.</i>

12
00:00:34,826 --> 00:00:37,370
- [Lorna] <i>Jeffrey Matulak?</i>
- Present, ma'am.

13
00:00:37,454 --> 00:00:40,498
[Lorna] <i>There’s a lot that needs cleaning</i>
<i>in the back area.</i>

14
00:00:40,582 --> 00:00:44,669
<i>I want it cleaned thoroughly, okay?</i>

15
00:00:44,753 --> 00:00:45,879
[warped beep]

16
00:00:45,962 --> 00:00:47,213
What’s this?

17
00:00:47,297 --> 00:00:49,090
Why does it need numbers?

18
00:00:49,174 --> 00:00:50,508
[Ibyang] <i>I don’t even like math.</i>

19
00:00:50,592 --> 00:00:51,885
‪PREVIOUSLY

20
00:00:51,968 --> 00:00:53,136
<i>Master Grumpy?</i>

21
00:00:53,219 --> 00:00:54,345
Yes, keep quiet.

22
00:00:54,429 --> 00:00:55,972
- Is that you?
- Yes.

23
00:00:56,473 --> 00:00:57,766
Why is your hair different?

24
00:00:57,849 --> 00:01:00,643
- Ah, just keep your mouth shut.
- [Lorna] What’s happening?

25
00:01:00,727 --> 00:01:02,520
Why is there a child here?

26
00:01:02,604 --> 00:01:05,273
[Ibyang] <i>Do you have food there, madam?</i>

27
00:01:05,356 --> 00:01:06,316
[Atoy] <i>Unbelievable!</i>

28
00:01:06,399 --> 00:01:07,901
[Atoy] I told you to watch her.

29
00:01:07,984 --> 00:01:10,487
I rarely give you orders,
and she still managed to escape from you.

30
00:01:10,570 --> 00:01:12,864
[Karla] <i>We got carried away</i>
<i>playing basketball.</i>

31
00:01:12,947 --> 00:01:14,324
<i>I didn’t notice she bolted.</i>

32
00:01:14,407 --> 00:01:19,496
[Ibyang] <i>Big Sister Ame saved me</i>
<i>when the orphanage burned down!</i>

33
00:01:19,579 --> 00:01:22,916
[brazen music continues]

34
00:01:27,587 --> 00:01:31,132
[hooters honking]

35
00:01:31,216 --> 00:01:33,134
[melancholic music playing]

36
00:01:33,218 --> 00:01:35,804
[hooters honking]

37
00:01:41,851 --> 00:01:44,687
Ah, uhm, good day.

38
00:01:45,230 --> 00:01:48,108
Are you looking for a kitchen helper?

39
00:01:48,191 --> 00:01:50,110
I’m good in the kitchen.

40
00:01:50,193 --> 00:01:52,320
Here, I brought my resume.

41
00:01:52,403 --> 00:01:54,197
Maybe you’d like to check it.

42
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:57,033
Can you even reach the kitchen counter?

43
00:01:57,700 --> 00:01:58,701
You’re funny, girl.

44
00:01:58,785 --> 00:02:03,289
[melancholic music continues]

45
00:02:25,395 --> 00:02:26,229
Ibyang?

46
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:31,943
Ibyang?

47
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:34,654
Ibyang, what are you doing here?

48
00:02:34,737 --> 00:02:36,990
Later, okay?

49
00:02:37,740 --> 00:02:38,825
Ibyang.

50
00:02:40,285 --> 00:02:43,538
What’s going on? Someone’s sleeping here!

51
00:02:43,621 --> 00:02:44,622
Big Sister Ame!

52
00:02:46,791 --> 00:02:48,501
What are you doing here?

53
00:02:49,002 --> 00:02:51,462
I’m the one asking you.

54
00:02:51,546 --> 00:02:53,631
Weren’t you transferred
to another orphanage?

55
00:02:54,799 --> 00:02:56,384
Yes, sis.

56
00:02:56,467 --> 00:02:57,677
But…

57
00:02:59,137 --> 00:03:01,014
The people there are mean!

58
00:03:01,097 --> 00:03:02,765
And there are so many kids.

59
00:03:02,849 --> 00:03:04,517
It’s chaotic.

60
00:03:04,601 --> 00:03:08,062
So, I escaped to find you.

61
00:03:08,897 --> 00:03:10,064
You’re crazy.

62
00:03:10,565 --> 00:03:13,067
You’ll get into trouble doing that.

63
00:03:13,151 --> 00:03:15,445
Good thing no one kidnapped you here.

64
00:03:16,487 --> 00:03:19,032
They’re afraid of me.

65
00:03:19,866 --> 00:03:24,621
Good thing you found me.

66
00:03:25,204 --> 00:03:27,498
- It's a good thing.
- [gentle music playing]

67
00:03:27,582 --> 00:03:29,918
Come on. I’ll take you back there.

68
00:03:30,001 --> 00:03:31,794
Just be patient.

69
00:03:31,878 --> 00:03:34,172
You don’t have a choice.

70
00:03:34,255 --> 00:03:37,217
It’s dangerous for you
to sleep on the streets.

71
00:03:37,842 --> 00:03:41,387
Big Sis, I don’t want to go back there.

72
00:03:41,471 --> 00:03:44,474
I want to be with you.

73
00:03:44,974 --> 00:03:47,143
You’re the only one who’s nice to me.

74
00:03:47,227 --> 00:03:51,439
Ibyang, my life isn’t good
right now either.

75
00:03:51,522 --> 00:03:54,692
I lost my job because of the fire.

76
00:03:55,193 --> 00:03:56,569
I have no savings.

77
00:03:56,653 --> 00:03:58,238
Only debts.

78
00:03:58,905 --> 00:04:02,367
I can’t give you a good life.

79
00:04:02,450 --> 00:04:04,661
That’s okay.

80
00:04:04,744 --> 00:04:08,331
What’s important is you’re kind to me.

81
00:04:08,414 --> 00:04:12,001
And I want to be with you.

82
00:04:12,543 --> 00:04:16,089
Please, don’t give me away.

83
00:04:16,589 --> 00:04:18,633
[in English] Please.

84
00:04:19,676 --> 00:04:24,013
[somber music playing]

85
00:04:33,690 --> 00:04:36,109
Even though Big Sister Ame had no money,

86
00:04:36,734 --> 00:04:38,945
she still took me in.

87
00:04:39,529 --> 00:04:43,449
Sometimes we only ate once a day.

88
00:04:46,077 --> 00:04:50,373
But that was okay
because we were hungry together.

89
00:04:51,874 --> 00:04:54,002
[sniffles]

90
00:04:54,085 --> 00:04:56,379
She loves me very much.

91
00:04:59,841 --> 00:05:04,887
Even if I’m stubborn,
she never yells at me.

92
00:05:06,055 --> 00:05:11,185
Unlike Master Grumpy, who helps,

93
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:13,938
but has a bad attitude.

94
00:05:15,481 --> 00:05:19,861
That’s why I’ll do everything
to save Big Sister Ame.

95
00:05:21,237 --> 00:05:25,533
[somber music continues]

96
00:05:32,248 --> 00:05:33,166
Ibyang.

97
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:37,128
Ibyang, your Big Brother Atoy is kind too.

98
00:05:38,755 --> 00:05:43,217
That’s why he’s doing everything
to save your Big Sister Ame.

99
00:05:44,385 --> 00:05:45,261
Okay?

100
00:05:47,221 --> 00:05:49,015
I don’t want him anymore.

101
00:05:50,683 --> 00:05:52,935
I don’t want him anymore, miss.

102
00:05:55,146 --> 00:05:57,982
I don’t want to be with Master Grumpy.

103
00:05:59,108 --> 00:06:01,736
So, I hope he brings back Big Sister Ame,

104
00:06:01,819 --> 00:06:03,446
so I can leave this place.

105
00:06:03,529 --> 00:06:04,572
[Cita clicks tongue, sighs]

106
00:06:08,034 --> 00:06:12,205
[sobbing]

107
00:06:12,288 --> 00:06:16,375
[somber music continues]

108
00:06:18,377 --> 00:06:19,587
[sniffles]

109
00:06:28,179 --> 00:06:30,181
[deep breath]

110
00:06:30,264 --> 00:06:33,267
[suave music playing]

111
00:06:35,269 --> 00:06:36,145
[machine whirring]

112
00:06:36,229 --> 00:06:37,105
[swooshing]

113
00:06:37,188 --> 00:06:38,064
[cutting]

114
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:41,567
[machine whirring]

115
00:06:41,651 --> 00:06:42,985
[machine whirring]

116
00:06:43,069 --> 00:06:44,695
[gun cocks]

117
00:06:44,779 --> 00:06:46,364
[gunshots blasting]

118
00:06:46,447 --> 00:06:48,658
[machine whirring]

119
00:06:48,741 --> 00:06:50,743
[cutting]

120
00:06:52,870 --> 00:06:54,330
[metallic clink]

121
00:06:58,501 --> 00:06:59,961
[Lorna] Listen, all of you.

122
00:07:00,044 --> 00:07:01,712
I don’t want to repeat myself.

123
00:07:01,796 --> 00:07:04,298
We have back-to- back peak nights,

124
00:07:04,382 --> 00:07:06,509
so prepare yourselves.

125
00:07:07,677 --> 00:07:09,178
It’s payday today,

126
00:07:09,262 --> 00:07:12,557
so for sure they’ll be
burning money later.

127
00:07:13,141 --> 00:07:16,352
Tomorrow is Havana Friday Night,

128
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:20,815
so expect our D.O.M. patrons to flock in.

129
00:07:20,898 --> 00:07:21,941
Okay?

130
00:07:22,984 --> 00:07:26,237
Now, I don’t want anyone wandering

131
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:29,282
or acting stupid here on the main floor.

132
00:07:29,991 --> 00:07:33,244
When I call you, only then
should you come.

133
00:07:33,327 --> 00:07:36,330
And when I call you, you come immediately.

134
00:07:36,414 --> 00:07:38,332
I don’t want to be kept waiting.

135
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:39,584
Got it?

136
00:07:39,667 --> 00:07:40,543
- Yes, ma'am.
- Yes, ma'am.

137
00:07:40,626 --> 00:07:41,627
[Lorna] Okay.

138
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:45,882
For now, I need someone
to guard the gold card area.

139
00:07:45,965 --> 00:07:47,633
Two. I need two janitors.

140
00:07:47,717 --> 00:07:49,760
- [Lorna, indistinct]
- Ma’am, I’ll do it.

141
00:07:50,428 --> 00:07:51,345
You?

142
00:07:53,264 --> 00:07:54,891
You can’t.

143
00:07:54,974 --> 00:07:57,727
You’re new. You might mess up.

144
00:07:57,810 --> 00:07:59,395
You might cause problems.

145
00:07:59,479 --> 00:08:02,190
I want experienced ones. You, you.

146
00:08:02,273 --> 00:08:04,817
You two, okay? Do a good job.

147
00:08:04,901 --> 00:08:08,029
[sinister music playing]

148
00:08:08,112 --> 00:08:09,489
[phone rings]

149
00:08:09,989 --> 00:08:10,990
[phone beeps]

150
00:08:11,073 --> 00:08:13,993
[Lorna] Go on. Work.

151
00:08:15,119 --> 00:08:15,953
[man mutters]

152
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:20,374
[tense music playing]

153
00:08:20,458 --> 00:08:21,876
[Atoy] Bro, wow.

154
00:08:21,959 --> 00:08:27,423
Ma’am Lorna is really strict
about the gold card area.

155
00:08:28,424 --> 00:08:30,051
What’s in there?

156
00:08:30,134 --> 00:08:31,469
The big-time people.

157
00:08:31,552 --> 00:08:33,513
Just do a good job here,

158
00:08:34,138 --> 00:08:36,349
next time you’ll be assigned there.
It’s a win there.

159
00:08:36,432 --> 00:08:38,643
The customers tip big.

160
00:08:38,726 --> 00:08:40,728
Especially those betting on the fight.

161
00:08:42,271 --> 00:08:43,481
Fight?

162
00:08:44,273 --> 00:08:45,525
What kind of fight?

163
00:08:45,608 --> 00:08:48,402
Like boxing?

164
00:08:50,655 --> 00:08:51,906
[janitor] Yes, kind of.

165
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:55,451
But the fighters are dwarfs. It’s brutal.

166
00:08:55,535 --> 00:08:59,413
[dramatic music playing]

167
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:06,212
I heard some even die there.

168
00:09:06,295 --> 00:09:08,256
But it never makes the news.

169
00:09:08,339 --> 00:09:11,759
[dramatic music continues]

170
00:09:15,805 --> 00:09:20,935
[Datryl] No one else can help you
get out of here but yourself.

171
00:09:22,603 --> 00:09:26,941
[fire crackling]

172
00:09:27,024 --> 00:09:29,944
[pensive music playing]

173
00:09:34,699 --> 00:09:38,160
[inquisitive music playing]

174
00:09:45,126 --> 00:09:50,131
Darryl. Teach me how to fight.

175
00:09:50,214 --> 00:09:51,549
That’s it!

176
00:09:51,632 --> 00:09:54,385
That’s what we need here. Someone cocky.

177
00:09:56,512 --> 00:09:59,098
Like this. Let’s start with the basics.

178
00:09:59,599 --> 00:10:02,643
Stand like this, so you won’t fall easily.

179
00:10:05,855 --> 00:10:10,192
I don’t really know much,
but I still win my fights.

180
00:10:10,818 --> 00:10:13,487
Ah, is it like this? Am I doing it right?

181
00:10:13,571 --> 00:10:14,405
That’s fine.

182
00:10:14,488 --> 00:10:17,908
I just copy what I see in boxing matches.

183
00:10:17,992 --> 00:10:20,911
Your hands should always
be raised to your head.

184
00:10:20,995 --> 00:10:21,996
Like this.

185
00:10:22,079 --> 00:10:24,540
[mid-tempo music]

186
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:26,167
Like that?

187
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:27,960
Yes, that’s right.

188
00:10:28,461 --> 00:10:31,922
So, when you get punched,
your face won’t get hit directly.

189
00:10:37,261 --> 00:10:41,057
[laughs derisively]

190
00:10:44,268 --> 00:10:46,854
[Datryl] What’s
your problem again, Tessie?

191
00:10:46,937 --> 00:10:48,481
We’re just minding our business here.

192
00:10:48,564 --> 00:10:51,275
It’s just funny watching you both.

193
00:10:51,359 --> 00:10:54,028
One fool, one idiot.

194
00:10:54,111 --> 00:10:57,615
[laughing]

195
00:11:02,870 --> 00:11:04,914
We’ll see, Tessie.

196
00:11:04,997 --> 00:11:08,125
Next time we face each other,
I’ll knock you down.

197
00:11:08,209 --> 00:11:09,919
Really?

198
00:11:10,002 --> 00:11:12,088
So scary.

199
00:11:12,171 --> 00:11:15,591
[laughing]

200
00:11:17,259 --> 00:11:18,552
Ignore her.

201
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:23,182
Throw a punch, Ame.

202
00:11:24,558 --> 00:11:28,521
[tense music playing]

203
00:11:30,481 --> 00:11:32,525
When you stand like this,

204
00:11:32,608 --> 00:11:35,778
this is where you should
draw your punch from.

205
00:11:36,570 --> 00:11:38,447
Are you right-handed or left-handed?

206
00:11:38,531 --> 00:11:41,033
- Right… Right-handed.
- [Darryl] Yes!

207
00:11:41,117 --> 00:11:44,245
So, your left foot should be in front.

208
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:50,084
[Darryl] Like that.

209
00:11:51,210 --> 00:11:55,172
[intense music continues]

210
00:12:00,094 --> 00:12:03,889
Do you know who owns this bar?

211
00:12:03,973 --> 00:12:06,517
I know there are many owners.

212
00:12:07,309 --> 00:12:10,729
But the biggest boss is the one
they call Boss Alpha.

213
00:12:11,897 --> 00:12:14,567
Does he watch the fights?

214
00:12:14,650 --> 00:12:18,487
I don’t know. They say he’s often abroad.

215
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:21,449
You know what?
Don’t even think about them.

216
00:12:21,532 --> 00:12:24,952
What’s important is you
give them a good fight.

217
00:12:26,454 --> 00:12:30,541
There’s one customer here,
I’ve never seen him,

218
00:12:31,834 --> 00:12:34,962
but I know he always bets big on me.

219
00:12:35,045 --> 00:12:36,422
[in English] Big time.

220
00:12:36,505 --> 00:12:39,800
I only know him by the name ROJO.

221
00:12:40,468 --> 00:12:45,514
He’s my favorite,
because whenever I win, he sends food.

222
00:12:45,598 --> 00:12:46,807
He’s kind too.

223
00:12:48,726 --> 00:12:52,563
He’s only kind because, of course,
they profit from us.

224
00:12:53,397 --> 00:12:58,861
But I suspect they’re doing
other illegal things.

225
00:13:03,782 --> 00:13:04,783
[Red] Vladimir.

226
00:13:05,576 --> 00:13:08,204
- [in English] Red! How are you?
- [in English] Welcome to my humble home.

227
00:13:08,287 --> 00:13:10,414
- [in English] Ah, it’s beautiful.
- [in English] How was your flight?

228
00:13:10,498 --> 00:13:13,959
[in English] Very good.
At the same time, very sexy.

229
00:13:14,502 --> 00:13:17,087
[in English] But, uh,
I have a gift for you.

230
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:18,839
[in English] You can choose one
if you want.

231
00:13:18,923 --> 00:13:21,133
[clicks tongue, in English]
I have to check them out first.

232
00:13:21,217 --> 00:13:22,259
[Vladimir, in English] Sure.

233
00:13:23,177 --> 00:13:24,094
[in English] Go ahead.

234
00:13:24,929 --> 00:13:29,350
- [Red sniffs]
- [inquisitive music playing]

235
00:13:35,523 --> 00:13:36,899
[Red sniffs]

236
00:13:41,070 --> 00:13:45,616
- [Vladimir, English] How do you like them?
- [in English] Ah… I like…

237
00:13:45,699 --> 00:13:48,911
[music intensifies]

238
00:13:51,539 --> 00:13:54,583
Oh? Um…

239
00:13:55,918 --> 00:13:57,920
[in English] Martina, Vladimir.
Vladimir, my wife.

240
00:13:58,003 --> 00:13:59,838
[in English] Martina,
it’s a pleasure to meet you.

241
00:13:59,922 --> 00:14:01,215
[in English] Very beautiful.

242
00:14:02,675 --> 00:14:06,929
[in English] So… ladies.

243
00:14:08,097 --> 00:14:10,933
[in English] What else, aside from
spreading your legs, do you do for money?

244
00:14:11,016 --> 00:14:13,143
Psst. Are you serious?

245
00:14:13,227 --> 00:14:14,270
[in English] What?

246
00:14:15,729 --> 00:14:16,647
[in English] You--

247
00:14:17,147 --> 00:14:20,025
[in English] You do know that you could
also use your mouths for speaking, right?

248
00:14:21,610 --> 00:14:22,486
[clears throat]

249
00:14:24,738 --> 00:14:26,866
[in English] Vladimir is part
of the Black Meridian.

250
00:14:27,783 --> 00:14:29,910
He’s the biggest supplier
of women in Asia.

251
00:14:29,994 --> 00:14:32,997
I need him because I have many clients
who need Filipina women.

252
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,039
[in English] Understand?

253
00:14:34,123 --> 00:14:35,374
[in English] I don’t care.

254
00:14:35,916 --> 00:14:38,794
[in English] This is my house.
Do your business somewhere else.

255
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:40,796
- [in English] Um, it’s okay.
- [sniffs]

256
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:44,425
[in English] We can find
another place to do business.

257
00:14:44,508 --> 00:14:47,803
[in English] How about we find a place
where we can meet Manny Pacquiao?

258
00:14:47,887 --> 00:14:48,804
[in English] You know any?

259
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:51,932
[in English] I actually know a place.

260
00:14:52,016 --> 00:14:55,269
- [Vladimir, in English] Oh, let’s go.
- [in English] Yeah. Let’s go.

261
00:14:55,352 --> 00:14:57,730
[tense dramatic music playing]

262
00:14:59,857 --> 00:15:00,691
[Red, in English] The girls?

263
00:15:00,774 --> 00:15:03,027
[in English] Ah! Girls, shall we?

264
00:15:03,819 --> 00:15:08,073
[tense music playing]

265
00:15:10,492 --> 00:15:11,452
[Vladimir, in English] I’ll grab you guys.

266
00:15:15,456 --> 00:15:17,583
[MC] Okay. Listen, all of you.

267
00:15:18,083 --> 00:15:20,127
These are the fights tonight.

268
00:15:20,836 --> 00:15:25,007
After I announce the matches, get ready.

269
00:15:25,507 --> 00:15:28,344
When I call you,
I want you to move immediately.

270
00:15:29,595 --> 00:15:31,805
[in English] Okay. First fight.

271
00:15:31,889 --> 00:15:33,891
[in English] Arturo versus Nemuel.

272
00:15:37,728 --> 00:15:41,106
After that, Ame versus Pam.

273
00:15:42,316 --> 00:15:46,070
[unsettling music playing]

274
00:15:46,153 --> 00:15:47,488
Can I volunteer?

275
00:15:47,571 --> 00:15:50,282
I’ll fight Ame instead of Pam.

276
00:15:50,366 --> 00:15:51,867
And why would I do that?

277
00:15:52,534 --> 00:15:55,204
I’ve been annoyed with this woman
for a long time.

278
00:15:55,287 --> 00:16:00,584
I’ll make sure the audience
enjoys what I’ll do to her.

279
00:16:00,668 --> 00:16:02,962
[people jeering]

280
00:16:03,045 --> 00:16:06,256
Okay, fine. You better mean it.

281
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:11,220
Yes, Boss. Not just a knockout,
prepare a body bag.

282
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:16,725
[tense music playing]

283
00:16:16,809 --> 00:16:19,979
Don’t mind her.
She’s just trying to scare you.

284
00:16:20,062 --> 00:16:22,898
Just remember everything
we practiced earlier.

285
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:27,027
I’m not afraid of her.

286
00:16:27,861 --> 00:16:32,241
If that Tessie is an obstacle
for me to see Ibyang again,

287
00:16:32,866 --> 00:16:34,410
she’s mistaken about
who she’s messing with.

288
00:16:36,745 --> 00:16:39,957
[intense music playing]

289
00:16:46,588 --> 00:16:47,548
[Tonet] Come in.

290
00:16:47,631 --> 00:16:49,800
Good thing you’re back, Ibyang.

291
00:16:49,883 --> 00:16:52,011
We were so worried about you.

292
00:16:52,594 --> 00:16:55,597
This child wandered a long way
from here, my goodness.

293
00:16:55,681 --> 00:16:57,891
Did you talk to Atoy, Ibyang?

294
00:16:57,975 --> 00:17:00,936
I don’t want to talk about
that Master Grumpy.

295
00:17:01,937 --> 00:17:04,148
He’s grumpy and heartless.

296
00:17:04,815 --> 00:17:07,901
I hope he finds Big Sister Ame soon,

297
00:17:07,985 --> 00:17:10,362
so I can leave this place.

298
00:17:10,446 --> 00:17:13,282
[somber music playing]

299
00:17:13,365 --> 00:17:18,078
Ibyang, don’t say that.

300
00:17:18,162 --> 00:17:20,748
You know, I do understand you.

301
00:17:21,582 --> 00:17:24,501
I know it’s hard to get along
with your Big Brother Atoy.

302
00:17:26,211 --> 00:17:27,379
[chuckles]

303
00:17:27,463 --> 00:17:32,176
But I know he regrets what he said to you.

304
00:17:33,844 --> 00:17:36,930
And, whatever happens, I promise you this…

305
00:17:37,639 --> 00:17:40,476
Your Big Brother Atoy will never stop

306
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:43,228
until he finds your Big Sis Ame.

307
00:17:44,271 --> 00:17:46,190
That’s the kind of person he is.

308
00:17:47,608 --> 00:17:48,442
Huh?

309
00:17:48,525 --> 00:17:51,070
[hopeful music playing]

310
00:18:00,537 --> 00:18:04,458
[indistinct chatter in the background]

311
00:18:04,541 --> 00:18:06,210
[upbeat music playing]

312
00:18:06,293 --> 00:18:07,419
[phone chimes]

313
00:18:12,758 --> 00:18:16,386
IBYANG HAS COME HOME

314
00:18:20,390 --> 00:18:23,685
[upbeat music continues]

315
00:18:26,563 --> 00:18:30,400
[suspicious music playing]

316
00:18:37,491 --> 00:18:39,076
[beeping]

317
00:18:39,159 --> 00:18:43,205
[mysterious music playing]

318
00:18:50,379 --> 00:18:52,005
[beeping]

319
00:18:54,091 --> 00:18:58,387
[suspicious music continues]

320
00:19:09,106 --> 00:19:13,026
[upbeat club music playing]

321
00:19:25,873 --> 00:19:26,999
- [man] Oops.
- [suave music playing]

322
00:19:27,666 --> 00:19:29,626
You stay here. I’ll stay there.

323
00:19:30,794 --> 00:19:31,753
[in English] Come on.

324
00:19:32,254 --> 00:19:33,213
[in English] Thank you.

325
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:38,218
[brazen music playing]

326
00:19:43,724 --> 00:19:47,853
[brazen music playing]

327
00:20:04,286 --> 00:20:08,373
- [indistinct chattering]
- [inquisitive music playing]

328
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:12,711
[brazen music playing]

329
00:20:18,592 --> 00:20:22,554
[upbeat music playing]

330
00:20:27,684 --> 00:20:32,231
- [bell rings]
- [crowd cheering]

331
00:20:32,314 --> 00:20:33,649
‪[energetic club music playing]

332
00:20:34,608 --> 00:20:37,527
[crowd buzzing]

333
00:20:38,445 --> 00:20:41,573
[crowd buzzing]

334
00:20:44,076 --> 00:20:45,452
- [bell rings]
- [man] Sir Red is here.

335
00:20:46,036 --> 00:20:46,870
[man, in English] Welcome, Sir Red.

336
00:20:46,954 --> 00:20:48,038
[attendant] Wait, I’ll get your table.

337
00:20:48,121 --> 00:20:48,956
[in English] Yup.

338
00:20:50,457 --> 00:20:51,416
[man shouts]

339
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:54,878
- [crowd buzzing, clapping]
- [Red sniffs]

340
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:02,261
[crowd cheering, clapping]

341
00:21:03,303 --> 00:21:05,597
[crowd cheering]

342
00:21:06,390 --> 00:21:08,183
[in English] What is this place, Red?

343
00:21:10,352 --> 00:21:11,687
[in English] You’re gonna love this place.

344
00:21:12,396 --> 00:21:16,441
[in English] It’s a, uh,
battle of mini gladiators.

345
00:21:18,193 --> 00:21:20,153
- [in English] I like.
- [chuckles]

346
00:21:20,862 --> 00:21:21,697
[man, in English] Welcome, Sir Red.

347
00:21:21,780 --> 00:21:23,865
- [man] Here, please.
- Okay.

348
00:21:24,658 --> 00:21:25,993
- [sighs]
- [indistinct speech]

349
00:21:28,829 --> 00:21:29,788
[sighs]

350
00:21:29,871 --> 00:21:33,083
[tense music playing]

351
00:21:35,168 --> 00:21:39,256
[energetic music playing]

352
00:21:50,392 --> 00:21:54,354
[loud puff]

353
00:21:57,941 --> 00:21:59,192
[loud puff]

354
00:22:00,485 --> 00:22:04,364
[energetic music playing]

355
00:22:08,535 --> 00:22:09,745
[loud puff]

356
00:22:11,580 --> 00:22:12,914
[loud puff]

357
00:22:14,124 --> 00:22:15,459
- [glasses shatter]
- That’s been going on for a while!

358
00:22:15,542 --> 00:22:18,378
- [waiter] Sorry, sir.
- [patron] This place is getting crazy.

359
00:22:21,089 --> 00:22:25,469
- [dramatic music playing]
- [electronic blipping]

360
00:22:31,349 --> 00:22:33,351
Miss, I really can’t find Ibyang.

361
00:22:33,435 --> 00:22:35,103
- Huh?
- Not even in the kitchen or the restroom.

362
00:22:35,187 --> 00:22:38,065
Why? Karla, did Ibyang escape
from you again?

363
00:22:38,148 --> 00:22:40,609
- [Atoy] <i>Where is she?</i>
- [Ibyang] This suits me well, huh?

364
00:22:40,692 --> 00:22:41,902
[metallic clicking]

365
00:22:41,985 --> 00:22:43,570
[brazen music playing]

366
00:22:43,653 --> 00:22:46,323
‪UP NEXT

367
00:22:46,406 --> 00:22:49,242
They say he has a client
in Japan. Make him happy.

368
00:22:49,326 --> 00:22:51,828
Then your life will change, right?

369
00:22:51,912 --> 00:22:53,914
- Can you do my makeup again?
- Of course.

370
00:22:54,790 --> 00:22:55,874
[Tonet] <i>What look are you going for?</i>

371
00:22:59,795 --> 00:23:01,254
Bring my keep bottle here, okay?

372
00:23:02,756 --> 00:23:06,176
[brazen music continues]

373
00:23:11,139 --> 00:23:12,933
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
